 So, now, we've talked about the both each other.

00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:14.000
 And, of course, many of you, I mean, you all know the both each other, both each other.

00:04:14.000 --> 00:04:19.000
 And both each other is generally the foundation and the center column of the Buddha's teaching.

00:04:19.000 --> 00:04:23.000
 And, therefore, I mean, entirely Buddha's teaching.

00:04:23.000 --> 00:04:28.000
 Eighty-four thousand different teachings or nayana teachings,

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:33.000
 all like three basket teachings, all three turning the wheel of Dharma.

00:04:33.000 --> 00:04:37.000
 Everything is really best on this both each other.

00:04:37.000 --> 00:04:42.000
 There is nothing else Buddha spoke besides both each other's teachings that way, all the way.

00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:45.000
 And both each other, what is both each other?

00:04:45.000 --> 00:04:48.000
 It's nature. Nature teaches.

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:52.000
 Nature of ourself, nature of others.

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:57.000
 And our brain, the harmonizing, how beautiful ourself and others,

00:04:57.000 --> 00:05:01.000
 and that is really the teaching of both each other.

00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:05.000
 And we all know, we are in samsara, as we call it samsara.

00:05:05.000 --> 00:05:10.000
 Samsara has a lot of bumpy situations, a lot of challenges.

00:05:10.000 --> 00:05:14.000
 Bumpy goes up and down, and there are so many challenges, difficulties,

00:05:14.000 --> 00:05:22.000
 unpleasant things come up because all this is a leg of contracting to the natural

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:27.000
 and a leg of also both each other, understanding.

00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:33.000
 And that's why all these troubles and difficulties, bumpy situations arise.

00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:39.000
 Therefore, both each other is just so special and just so beautiful

00:05:39.000 --> 00:05:46.000
 because it's touching to the core of our nature and our beauty and the beauties of others.

00:05:46.000 --> 00:05:50.000
 And we begin this value and importance of everything.

00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:56.000
 In the Vedayana teaching, often teaching tells everything is a purity status.

00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:02.000
 But also, if we have the true love and compassion to everyone,

00:06:02.000 --> 00:06:06.000
 that is the key to open the door of everything is a purity status.

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:10.000
 Nothing is unpleasant, nothing is impure.

00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:17.000
 When you have love and compassion, you see everything is so beautiful, so special.

00:06:17.000 --> 00:06:20.000
 And that is both each other.

00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:27.000
 Both each other, of course, I think you all know, but again, is reminded to each other, us.

00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:33.000
 It's both each other, it's love, both each other is compassion, and both each other is wisdom.

00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:40.000
 Vastra, this three beautiful components of the nature of the mind is known as both each other.

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:47.000
 In fact, there is no enlightenment, no Buddhahood beside this both each other.

00:06:47.000 --> 00:06:53.000
 Therefore, the greatest teacher, Gaurabh and Masambhav mentioned these three.

00:06:53.000 --> 00:06:58.000
 Love and compassion, Vastra, are the mind of the Buddha.

00:06:58.000 --> 00:07:00.000
 This is the mind of the Buddha.

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:06.000
 One we are with the authentic true love.

00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:08.000
 We are with the mind of the Buddha.

00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:13.000
 One we are authentically with the mind with compassion.

00:07:13.000 --> 00:07:17.000
 We are in that moment with the Buddha mind status.

00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:19.000
 Then similarly, wisdom.

00:07:19.000 --> 00:07:25.000
 So there is no Buddhahood or no enlightenment besides

00:07:25.000 --> 00:07:32.000
 loving kindness and compassion and a wisdom that has no discrimination.

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:37.000
 This is what is so important and so special.

00:07:37.000 --> 00:07:41.000
 It is our own nature of the mind.

00:07:41.000 --> 00:07:46.000
 It's not outside. Love is, as we all know, love is not going to come outside.

00:07:46.000 --> 00:07:49.000
 And compassion is not going to come outside.

00:07:49.000 --> 00:07:54.000
 And all the wisdom has to be revealed within ourselves.

00:07:54.000 --> 00:07:59.000
 External will support, help, condition, their condition.

00:07:59.000 --> 00:08:02.000
 They can't really re-glorify those qualities.

00:08:02.000 --> 00:08:09.000
 But true love, true compassion and wisdom that merge from the mind.

00:08:09.000 --> 00:08:14.000
 When we extend that light of love and compassion from our heart and mind,

00:08:14.000 --> 00:08:19.000
 we feel the power of love and compassion to ourselves.

00:08:19.000 --> 00:08:22.000
 Also others will feel that too.

00:08:22.000 --> 00:08:28.000
 Therefore, this bodhicitta is just the foundation, center column,

00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:32.000
 and the embodiment teaching of the Buddha Shakyamuni.

00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:36.000
 And as well as practice of the Buddha and Gopin Masambha,

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:41.000
 all those great lineage masters, all those great practitioners

00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:45.000
 who practice this bodhicitta and reach higher realization

00:08:45.000 --> 00:08:48.000
 and discover this, become the Buddha.

00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:51.000
 With all the bodhicitta, there is no enlightenment.

00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:54.000
 And no happiness, no joy and no peace.

00:08:54.000 --> 00:09:00.000
 And therefore, this bodhicitta is just really very, very special

00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:03.000
 and very, very crucial.

00:09:03.000 --> 00:09:06.000
 We like to bring peace, happiness to ourselves.

00:09:06.000 --> 00:09:11.000
 And also we like to bring happy and joy, peace to other beings.

00:09:11.000 --> 00:09:18.000
 Therefore, this bodhicitta is very, very, very special and very important.

00:09:21.000 --> 00:09:22.000
 Thank you.

